isp water could only be considered a blessing from Tunare.  Zephire drank deeply, tipping his head back and letting the almost frigid water dribble down his face and neck, and doing so revealed the deep red war berries hanging from the dark Ironwood tree.  &quot;Perfect!  Tunare is indeed with me on this hunt.&quot;  Smiling now he gathered some togeather and slowly sang the song taught to him by his father, a rythmic chant that called upon the land for power and protection, and crushed the berries to form the deep blood colored face paint of a Ranger about kill.  Still sensing the Orcs through the foliage, and knowing it would be many hours yet before the sun set and they would travel, Zephire felt he had time to honor his ancestors and call to the forest for protection.<br>
  While doing this he thought on his prey.  A duo of Orcs traveling swiftly from the borders of Kelethin.  In their spore Zephire traced accents from Felwith, a days travel along a well used highway from the main lift.  Zephire wondered indeed what these two would be doing so deep into Elven territory.<br>
  A sharp snap of breaking branch brought him instantly into focus, spinning round and drawing the long blood knife from it's worn sheath.  But the action was never completed, and the knife fell to the ground as Zephire's world went black with the impact of something cruel and heavy against the side of his head. <p></p><i>Edited by <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uzephire.showPublicProfile>Zephire</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 3/23/00 3:19:46 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uaeani.showPublicProfile>Aeani</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalRainbow.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member of Brell</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(3/21/00 2:24:18 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.teleport.com/~ggarren/aeani.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Prelude to a Sentinel</span><hr size=1> Ouch.  Pretty good short story so far =)<br>
