<br>
&quot;Kroongth!  Ung kra da!&quot; And with that Zephire was yanked savagly to a sitting position by rough and horny Orc talons, thick and jagged nails biting into his flesh.  Almost passing out from the pain of sudden movement, a hard swing caught him in the chin dazzing him and bringing blackness to bear again.  But total blackness didn't come to him.  He was again hauled to a sitting position as an Orc grabbed his face and sqeezed on Zephires jaw muscles forcing his mouth open.  Foul and burning liquid was sloshed down his throat, immediately causing his eyes to water and face to flush.<br>
<br>
&quot;There.&quot; Zephire whipped his head to the left in surprise at hearing civil Elven tounge spoken, to be rewarded by yet another flash of pain in his head.  &quot;Dargth en choten wig.&quot; said the cultured voice, and more liquid was forced down Zephire's gullut.  Recoving from his latest attempted drowning, Zephire heard light, firm footfalls circle him from left to right.  &quot;You're quite lucky I showed when I did little forest mouse.  These fellows here were quite interested in consuming you to break the day fast.&quot;  Zephire surveyed the &quot;fellows&quot; Not two Orcs anymore, but 5.  Two huge in comparison to the others, and not of a cut that Zephire had seen before on the previous Orcs he hunted on the borders to Kelethin.  Huge did them a disservice (if such a thing could be done to an Orc), with black mail upon their breasts and well honed swords at their sides.  Each wore a bright steel helm with the image of a snarling Orc face painted on its crest.  Rivaling Zephire in height and build these two were clearly some higher form of Orc he had never come across or heard of.  They eyed him with a cool easiness of a wolf who knows without a doubt the rabbits leg is broken.  Zephire tried not to look like a rabbit.<br>
<br>
The cultured voice spoke again. &quot;But what I need from you won't take many breaths, and they will still have time to prepare you for their midnight rations.&quot;  A small laughter, almost childlike, broke from the voice.  Zephire was overwhelmed as the voice dipped near him and stiffled him with the sickly sweet smell Zephire could not discren earlier. Turning slightly he caught sight of who the voice belonged to, and would have leapt clean to the Butcher Block pass had he not been bound.  He only succeeded in launching a couple of feet into the air with fright and crashing to the ground, hitting his head on the exact spot as his previous injury.  Quickly the darkness enveloped him, but not so fast that one word registered and was spat from his lips in a shill cry, &quot;Drow!&quot;  <p></p><i>Edited by <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uzephire.showPublicProfile>Zephire</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 3/23/00 3:33:47 am<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.showMessage?topicID=6.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.showMessage?topicID=4.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.threadControl?topicID=12.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=12.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=12.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop 